-- Bank of China's Li Says Yuan Overseas Usage Should Rise, Financial Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-27T23:25:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/bank-of-china-s-li-says-yuan-overseas-usage-should-rise-financial-reports.html

          
          
             Bank of China Ltd. President Li
Lihui said China should allow more foreign companies to sell
yuan-denominated bonds in China to increase the willingness of
people overseas to use the yuan, the Financial News reported.  
 The nation should also increase currency swaps with other
countries, Li was cited by the newspaper as saying. China should
also allow offshore yuan to re-enter the nation, Li was cited as
saying.  
 The Financial News newspaper is published by Chinaâ€™s
central bank.  
